(self.webpackChunkblog=self.webpackChunkblog||[]).push([[4828],{54828:n=>{n.exports="### script\n\n```js\n<html>\n  <body>\n    ...\n    <script src='a.js'><\/script>\n    <script src='b.js'><\/script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n```\n\n这段代码的含义是: 在文档资源执行完毕后, 然后 `a.js`、`b.js` 并发下载(浏览器机制), 顺序执行。\n\n下面这种写法与上面这种写法效果相同:\n\n```js\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <script src='a.js' defer><\/script>\n    <script src='b.js' defer><\/script>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    ...\n  </body>\n</html>\n```\n\n注意到关键词 `defer`, 它的特点如下:\n\n* 并发下载, `顺序执行`;\n* 渲染完再执行;\n\n再来看如下写法:\n\n```js\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <script src='a.js' async><\/script>\n    <script src='b.js' async><\/script>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    ...\n  </body>\n</html>\n```\n\n此时的关键词是 `async`, 它的特点如下:\n\n* 并发下载, `异步执行`(谁先下载好先执行谁);\n* 下载完就执行;"}}]);